# Minecraft two-agent management system

Read `MEMORY.md` and `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` when resuming work.

## Flow

User request → **Orchestrator** (`src/mcserver/orchestrator/service.py`, plain code) → Plugin Manager → `change_record` → Verifier (skip for info mode) → success or rollback.

## Hard constraints

- Orchestrator is deterministic Python — never introduce an LLM router.
- Plugin Manager and Verifier keep **separate** system prompts, tools, and message histories.
- Plugin installs search Hangar/Modrinth/SpigotMC and download jars; blocklist-only guardrail in prototype (`config.PLUGIN_BLOCKLIST`).
- Verifier has no write tools except `rollback_last_change`.
- Tool bodies live under `src/mcserver/tools/` (`stub/` orchestration, `plugins/` catalog, `process/` Java control).
- Application code lives in `src/mcserver/` — not repo root.

## Environment

- Runtime config lives in **`.env`** (loaded by `config.py`). When adding or changing env vars, **update `.env`** — not `.env.example` — unless you are only documenting a new variable for future clones.
- Never commit `.env` or copy secrets into `.env.example`.

## Contracts

- `ChangeRecord`: `{action, target, backup_path, timestamp, details?}`
- `VerifyResult`: `{healthy, reason}`
